TECH_PARAM_12.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: real time clock status - 1= OK, 0=not OK

TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Buoyancy reduction start day (relative to mission start day)
TECH_PARAM_13.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time in the day when the float first activated the valve during its descent

TECH_PARAM_14.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time in the day when the float first activated the valve during its descent

TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Cumulative valve actions at the surface
TECH_PARAM_15.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of solenoid valve actions at the surface until the crossing of the GAP threshold. Number computed by the float from previous cycles behaviour.

TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Additionnal valve actions at the surface
TECH_PARAM_16.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of solenoid valve actions at the surface until the crossing of the GAP threshold. These actions are performed after the NUMBER_CumulatedValveActionsAtSurfaceDuringDescent_COUNT previous ones.

TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Buoyancy inversion start day (relative to mission start day)
TECH_PARAM_17.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time when the float starts the buoyancy inversion phase when ice was detected during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_18.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time when the float starts the buoyancy inversion phase when ice was detected during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_19.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Time when the float starts the buoyancy inversion phase when ice was detected during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_20.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of solenoid valve actions needed to perform the buoyancy inversion phase when ice was detected during ascent.

TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent to parking depth start day (relative to mission start day)
TECH_PARAM_21.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time after the crossing  the gap threshold

TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent to parking depth start hour (resolution: 1 minute)
TECH_PARAM_22.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time after the crossing  the gap threshold (tenths of an hour since midnight)

TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: First stabilization day (relative to mission start day)
TECH_PARAM_23.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when first stabilization appears during descent to park

TECH_PARAM_24.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when first stabilization appears during descent to park

TECH_PARAM_25.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent to parking depth end day (relative to mission start day)
TECH_PARAM_25.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when park pressure is reached

TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent to parking depth end hour (resolution: 1 minute)
TECH_PARAM_26.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: time when park pressure is reached

TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions during descent to parking depth
TECH_PARAM_27.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_28.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during descent to parking depth
TECH_PARAM_28.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between the crossing  of the gap threshold and the end of descent at park pressure

TECH_PARAM_29.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: descent to park pressure: number of entries in margin around park pressure target - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target park pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_30.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy during park phase - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_31.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions during park phase

TECH_PARAM_32.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during drift at park
TECH_PARAM_32.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions while at park depth

TECH_PARAM_38.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions during descent to start profile pressure

TECH_PARAM_39.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of entrance in prof target range
TECH_PARAM_39.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: descent to profile pressure: number of entries in margin around profile pressure target  - specifically, how many times the float enters the band of pressure surrounding the target profile pressure (generally +/- 30db)

TECH_PARAM_40.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of repositions during drift at prof
TECH_PARAM_40.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: at profile pressure stand-by, number of times the float readjusts its buoyancy - using either the pump or EV

TECH_PARAM_41.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of valve actions during drift at prof
TECH_PARAM_41.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of valve actions while drifting at profile depth

TECH_PARAM_42.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during drift at prof
TECH_PARAM_42.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of pump actions during drift at profile depth.

TECH_PARAM_45.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: the time when the float moves the  pump to acquire additional buoyancy for surface drift.

TECH_PARAM_47.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: the time when the float moves the  pump to acquire additional buoyancy for surface drift.

TECH_PARAM_48.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during ascent
TECH_PARAM_48.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of pump actions between start and end of ascent

TECH_PARAM_49.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Ice detection flags (ISA detection : Bit 0, Satellite mask : Bit 1, Ascent hanging : Bit 2, ISA table overflow : Bit 7)
TECH_PARAM_49.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: The ice detection flag reported by the float (ISA detection : Bit 0, Satellite mask : Bit 1, Ascent hanging : Bit 2, ISA table overflow (overflow of the array used to store the CTD measurements to compute median values) : Bit 7) - see float manual for details.

TECH_PARAM_50.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: idem (this TECH information is used in TECH_AUX and TECH).
TECH_PARAM_50.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: aborted profile count - increments by one for each profile interrupted by ice detection. If units are 'bit' then represents the ice evasion record for the last 8 profiles with the latest profile in the least significant bit.

TECH_PARAM_51.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Grounding day  (relative to mission start day)

TECH_PARAM_54.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: First hanging day (relative to mission start)
TECH_PARAM_54.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Hanging start time (time when the float is hanged during ascent).

TECH_PARAM_55.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Hanging start time (time when the float is hanged during ascent).

TECH_PARAM_56.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Hanging start time (time when the float is hanged during ascent).

TECH_PARAM_57.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Emergency ascents - Internal count

TECH_PARAM_59.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Pressure that triggered the first emergency ascent

TECH_PARAM_60.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Number of pump actions during the first emergency ascent
TECH_PARAM_60.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Emergency ascent - pump actions at emergency depth

TECH_PARAM_61.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: First emergency ascent relative day (to 1st cycle day)

TECH_PARAM_63.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Flag reporting the status of the sensor board.

TECH_PARAM_64.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Rudics sessions which reached the time-out session duration.

TECH_PARAM_65.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb of errors during rudics session

TECH_PARAM_66.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: duration of the previous iridium session

TECH_PARAM_67.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: GPS Fix delay of current session
TECH_PARAM_67.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: the number of seconds required to obtain a GPS fix for a profile

TECH_PARAM_68.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Detailed auto-test for float hardware resulting in a detailed code for each tested sub-part (see manual)

TECH_PARAM_69.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Packet number for X type in descent
TECH_PARAM_69.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit <Sensor> data collected during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth).

TECH_PARAM_70.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Packet number for X type in drift
TECH_PARAM_70.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit <Sensor> data collected during the drift at park depth.

TECH_PARAM_71.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Packet number for X type in ascent
TECH_PARAM_71.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit <Sensor> data collected during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface.

TECH_PARAM_72.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of samples acquired by <Sensor> in the depth zone #<Z> during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth). Depth zone number: <Z> = 1..5

TECH_PARAM_74.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of samples acquired by <Sensor> in the depth zone #<Z> during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface. Depth zone number: <Z> = 1..5

TECH_PARAM_75.TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: X type status sensor (1: normal, 0 if problem)

TECH_PARAM_76.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure measured just before the float dives which is then used to correct pressure on board the float for the next profile.  Note: this is a relative offset. Autocorrected.

TECH_PARAM_77.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Last (shallowest) pumped raw pressure sample acquired during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface (i.e. just before the cut-off pressure where the pump is stopped) (in dbars).

TECH_PARAM_78.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Incremented for each sample the SUNA measures (it can be used to track frames, and recognize if frames were missed).

TECH_PARAM_79.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Incremented each time power is applied to SUNA (it can be used to notice if the SUNA was powered unintentionally between data collection events).

TECH_PARAM_80.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Incremented each time an error is encountered. The APF interface provides a mechanism to access error messages. If the error counter increases between frames, the operator or control system can retrieve the accumulated error message(s).

TECH_PARAM_81.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Voltage [V] measured inside SUNA via ADC. The voltage available to the SUNA just outside its power regulators. SUNA can operate on 6 to 18 VDC. This voltage allows the operator to monitor supply voltage, and in the case of a drop to make decisions on the continued operation of the SUNA.

TECH_PARAM_82.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Current [mA] measured inside SUNA via ADC. The current can be monitored to ascertain that all components are operating. A sudden drop or increase would indicate the failure of a system component.

TECH_PARAM_83.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of messages sent by the remote control and received by the iridium float

TECH_PARAM_84.TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: number of received messages which have been rejected by the float
